cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper deals with the debugging and verification of a concurrent logic language, which falls under the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) categories. The paper also discusses the use of abstract interpretation for debugging, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper presents examples of the efficacy of their approach, which involves analyzing program behavior, making it relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) category.
